### D.2 Resource Allocation Model

#### RACI Matrix for Key Deliverables

| Deliverable | PM | Architect | Security | Data Eng | DevOps | Business | Compliance |
|-------------|-----|-----------|----------|----------|---------|----------|------------|
| Architecture Design | A | R | C | C | I | C | I |
| Security Controls | A | C | R | I | C | I | C |
| Data Pipelines | A | C | I | R | C | C | I |
| Infrastructure | A | C | C | I | R | I | I |
| Compliance Docs | A | I | C | I | I | C | R |
| User Training | R | I | I | C | I | A | C |

**Legend:** R=Responsible, A=Accountable, C=Consulted, I=Informed

#### Staffing Plan with Industry Benchmarks

**Core Team Composition (Gartner Recommended):**
- **Project Manager**: 1.0 FTE (PMP certified, 10+ years)
- **Solution Architect**: 1.0 FTE (AWS Solutions Architect Professional)
- **Security Engineer**: 0.75 FTE (CISSP, AWS Security Specialty)
- **Data Engineers**: 2.0 FTE (AWS Data Analytics Specialty)
- **DevOps Engineer**: 1.0 FTE (AWS DevOps Professional)
- **Business Analyst**: 0.5 FTE (CBAP certified)
- **Compliance Officer**: 0.5 FTE (CISA, CAMS)

**Total FTE: 6.75** (Industry average for similar implementations: 5-8 FTE)

**Reference:** [Gartner Cloud Implementation Staffing Guide 2024](https://www.gartner.com/)‚Åµ‚Å¥

### D.3 Success Metrics and KPIs

#### OKR Framework Implementation

**Objective 1: Achieve Operational Excellence**
- **KR1**: 99.9% system availability (measured via CloudWatch)
- **KR2**: <5 second p95 query latency (measured via X-Ray)
- **KR3**: Zero critical security incidents (measured via GuardDuty)

**Objective 2: Deliver Business Value**
- **KR1**: 15% improvement in marketing ROI within 6 months
- **KR2**: 25% reduction in fraud detection false positives
- **KR3**: $2M+ cost savings from operational efficiency

**Objective 3: Ensure Compliance**
- **KR1**: 100% regulatory audit pass rate
- **KR2**: <24 hour compliance incident resolution
- **KR3**: 95%+ automated compliance monitoring coverage

**Reference:** [Measure What Matters by John Doerr](https://www.whatmatters.com/resources/what-is-an-okr-definition-examples)‚Åµ‚Åµ

### D.4 Risk Management Framework

#### Risk Register with Mitigation Strategies (ISO 31000 Aligned)

| Risk ID | Category | Risk Description | Probability | Impact | Risk Score | Mitigation Strategy | Owner | Status |
|---------|----------|------------------|-------------|--------|------------|-------------------|--------|---------|
| R001 | Technical | API integration failure | Medium (3) | High (4) | 12 | Implement circuit breakers, fallback mechanisms | Tech Lead | Open |
| R002 | Compliance | GDPR violation | Low (2) | Critical (5) | 10 | Privacy by design, DPO review | Compliance | Mitigating |
| R003 | Security | Data breach | Low (2) | Critical (5) | 10 | Defense in depth, penetration testing | CISO | Mitigating |
| R004 | Operational | Key personnel loss | Medium (3) | Medium (3) | 9 | Knowledge transfer, documentation | PMO | Open |
| R005 | Financial | Budget overrun | Medium (3) | Medium (3) | 9 | Monthly reviews, reserved capacity | Finance | Monitoring |

**Risk Response Strategies:**
- **Avoid**: Eliminate risk through design changes
- **Mitigate**: Reduce probability or impact
- **Transfer**: Insurance or contractual transfer
- **Accept**: Acknowledge and monitor

**Reference:** [ISO 31000:2018 Risk Management](https://www.iso.org/iso-31000-risk-management.html)‚Åµ‚Å∂

